article.headline: Coll. of Charleston 72, SIU-Edwardsville 66
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Andrew Goudelock scored 17 points to help The College of Charleston hold on to beat Southern Illinois-Edwardsville 72-66 in the first round of the ESPN/Charleston Classic on Friday. Charleston (1-0) made only 12 of 27 free throws, but compensated on the defensive end by forcing 24 turnovers en route to victory. Southern Illinois-Edwardsville (0-1) got 21 points from Mark Yelovich and 19 from Barry Wellington, who scored 14 of his 19 points in the first half on 5 of 7 shooting from the field. The game was Southern Illinois-Edwardsville's Division-I debut. In a game that was close throughout, Goudelocks running jump shot from the lane with 48 seconds to play all but clinched it for Charleston. Charleston will play Temple (1-0) tommorow at 2 p.m. in the second round of the tournament with the winner advancing to the championship game at 4 p.m. on Sunday.
